title: Philadelphia commuter trains crash head-on, four people injured (VIDEO, PHOTOS)
text:
Philadelphia commuter trains crash head-on, four people injured (VIDEO, PHOTOS)   15:17 Edited time: 21 Feb, 2017 15:56 Get short URL The crash happened just before 8:30am local time. @rob_el_train / Instagram Two commuter trains collided head-on in Philadelphia on Tuesday, injuring four people. The crash happened near the 69th Street Terminal during the city’s busy morning commute. Trends Viral 
"There are [probably] about a half a dozen cars that are involved as a result of the crash," Upper Darby Police Department Superintendent Michael Chitwood told CBS . 
The trains were empty when they collided, but minor injuries occurred when one of the cars toppled onto a separate parked car that housed a homeless man. All the other injured parties are reported to be workers from the Southeastern Pennsylvania Transportation Authority (SEPTA). 
A total of four people have been hospitalized, but their injuries are not serious. Trains off the tracks at #SEPTA 69th Street Terminal. @KYWNewsradio pic.twitter.com/d1K3BrIIVM — Tim Jimenez (@TimJRadio) February 21, 2017 
Neither train was traveling at high speed at the time of the crash, which occurred in a rail yard. Upper Darby police asked people to avoid the train terminal. A post shared by rob williams (@rob_el_train) on Feb 21, 2017 at 5:23am PST A post shared by Chris Yauger (@do_you_know_yauger) on Feb 21, 2017 at 6:10am PST A post shared by Little King Trashmouth (@katespenser) on Feb 21, 2017 at 5:58am PST Septa Terminal-reports of 2 trains colliding. Please avoid Septa 69th Terminal. — Upper Darby Police (@UDPolice) February 21, 2017 
SEPTA said investigators are combing the scene before the trains involved can be removed. A post shared by Mark Wilson (@mrwilsoncpa) on Feb 21, 2017 at 5:18am PST A post shared by Christian (@thiswheelshallexplode) on Feb 21, 2017 at 5:32am PST
